  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> in half and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned</p>\n<p>Once browned, set aside on a plate</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Wash the <strong>leek</strong><strong>s</strong><strong> </strong>carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> of <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>soft cheese</strong> to the <strong>stock</strong> and give it a good mix up <span class=\"text-highlight\">–</span> this is your <strong>creamy chicken stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and <strong>creamy stock</strong> to an <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>oven-proof dish</strong></span> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> browned</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to the dish </p>\n<p>Put the dish in the oven for 20 min or until the <strong>chicken</strong> is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Meanwhile, use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill! </span></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-chicken-leek-casserole-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy chicken &amp; leek bake</strong> over the<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong> brown rice</strong></span></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
